Sixth Avenue, west side, north from W. 45th Street. The buildings adjoining the corner are to be demolished for a new structure to house a new "Automat;"
view 2 is limited to these.
No. 3 is a later view of the same location. Note the Rockefeller Center buildings at the right. The "El" line in the center of the Avenue will be torn down in 1939.

View 3: March 22, 1934
